summary: The collaboration aims to support customers throughout the product development lifecycle of next-generation vehicle technologies.

headline: Jabil (JBL): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Jabil currently trades at $164.60 and has been a dream stock for shareholders. It’s returned 465% since May 2020, blowing past the S&P 500’s 97.3% gain. The company has also beaten the index over the past six months as its stock price is up 25.5% thanks to its solid quarterly results.
